Type: Package
Package: mfsusieR
Title: Multi-Outcome Functional Regression with the Sum of Single Effects Model
Version: 0.0.1
Date: 2026-04-25
Authors@R: c(
    person("Anjing", "Liu", role = "aut"),
    person("William R. P.", "Denault", role = "aut"),
    person("Gao", "Wang", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "wang.gao@columbia.edu"))
Description: Bayesian variable selection for functional regression
    problems with one or many outcomes. Each outcome may be a scalar
    or a curve sampled at a grid of positions. The method is built
    on the 'susieR' backbone via S3 dispatch and uses a wavelet-based
    functional prior so a variable that affects several spatially
    correlated positions is jointly identified. Motivated by molecular
    QTL fine-mapping, where outcomes are genome-scale molecular traits
    such as DNA methylation profiles and chromatin accessibility
    tracks; applies to any functional regression problem with
    sparsely-active variables.
